The paper deals with anomaly detection in communication networks, which is a topic that falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The paper also involves probabilistic modeling and regression analysis, which are techniques commonly used in machine learning and artificial intelligence (cs.AI, cs.LG). The use of sensor network data suggests that the paper may also be relevant to the sub-category of networking and internet architecture (cs.NI), while the focus on communication activity could place it in the sub-category of social and information networks (cs.SI).
